Uranium mines have been trying
to get in there for a while,

00:10:40.872 --> 00:10:43.408
they've been fended off
for about 20 years.

00:10:43.408 --> 00:10:45.344
But it's something
that's not going to go away

00:10:45.344 --> 00:10:47.779
anytime soon if we don't keep
a close eye on it.

00:10:47.779 --> 00:10:49.448
<i> The river on the other hand,</i>

00:10:49.448 --> 00:10:51.082
<i> we may have not done
 the best job</i>

00:10:51.082 --> 00:10:52.918
<i> of maintaining it
 through the Canyon.</i>

00:10:52.918 --> 00:10:55.087
<i> Now the water color here
 is emerald green,</i>

00:10:55.087 --> 00:10:56.855
<i> it looks beautiful,
 but it is not very natural,</i>

00:10:56.855 --> 00:10:58.791
<i> and it just represents
 how we have changed</i>

00:10:58.791 --> 00:11:00.792
<i> the dynamic of this river
 and of course that</i>

00:11:00.792 --> 00:11:04.530
<i> clear waters eroding a lot
 of natural sand and sediment.</i>

00:11:04.530 --> 00:11:07.132
<i> Now, this is one of
 the most storied rapids,</i>

00:11:07.132 --> 00:11:09.635
<i> this is called the V-wave,
